'''Martino Bassi''' (1542–1591) was an [[Italy|Italian]] architect active in the [[Renaissance]] period, mainly in [[Milan]]. He was born in [[Seregno]] near [[Milan]]. He was involved in a public dispute regarding the baptistery of the [[Cathedral of Milan]]. He helped build the imposing facade of [[Santa Maria presso San Celso]]. He also built the church of [[Santa Maria al Paradiso (Milan)|Santa Maria al Paradiso]].<!--
