'''Domenico Auria''' (active 16th century) was an [[Italy|Italian]] architect and sculptor of the [[Renaissance]] period, active in [[Naples]]. He was a pupil of [[Marliano da Nola]]. He is also known as ''Giovanni Domenico'' or ''Giovan Domenico Auria'', or ''Domenico d'Auria''.
