[[Image:Heliga Trefaldighetskyrkan exteriör cropped.jpg|thumb|200px|[[Trinity Church, Kristianstad]]]]
'''Lorenz van Steenwinckel''' (1585–1619) was a [[Flanders|Flemish]]-[[Denmark|Danish]] [[architect]] and [[sculptor]], son of [[Hans van Steenwinckel the Elder]] and brother of [[Hans van Steenwinckel the Younger]]. From 1613, he was responsible for numerous projects commissioned by [[Christian IV of Denmark|Christian IV]]. Christian IV's Chapel at [[Roskilde Cathedral]] and the [[Børsen|Stock Exchange]] in [[Copenhagen]] were among his many projects underway when he died in 1619, only 34 years old. The projects were completed by his brother Hans van Steenwinckel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denstoredanske.dk/Kunst_og_kultur/Arkitektur/Ren%C3%A6ssance/Lorenz_van_Steenwinckel|title=Lorenz van Steenwinckelket|publisher=Gyldendal|accessdate=2009-11-26}}</ref>

