'''Antonio da Lonate''' (born  1456-1457, [[Lonate Pozzolo]] - died after 1541, [[Milan]]) was an Italian [[architect]] who is known for his [[Renaissance architecture]]. A follower of [[Donato Bramante]], his works were designed in the [[High Renaissance]] style. Among the works attributed to him are the alter at the [[Basilica of San Magno]] in Legnano and the [[Vigevano Cathedral]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fmboschetto.it/Lonate_Pozzolo/altri_da_Lonate.htm|title=Dedicato ad Antonio da Lonate, architetto della cerchia dell'Amadeo|work=La Nona Campana|date=September 2006|author=G. D. Oltrona Visconti}}</ref>

