'''Lorenzo Vázquez de Segovia''' was a 15th-century [[Spain|Spanish]] [[architect]] and [[Construction worker|builder]] noted for completing the [[Santa Cruz Palace]] in 1491 in [[Valladolid]] and a number of other handsome buildings in the [[Castile (historical region)|Castile]] region of western [[Spain]] ([[Palace of the Dukes of Medinaceli (Cogolludo)]]).

